						               													<description>Crash Factor is a truly strategic pure balancing game played with calibrated weights.&amp;#10;Players take turns in a race to be rid of their &amp;quot;fleet&amp;quot; of varied weights by playing them onto a balancing gameboard into risk-reward zones.&amp;#10;Causing a crash or being unable to make a play during the game adds a dangerous penalty piece to the fleet.&amp;#10;A concentric &amp;quot;Crash Factor&amp;quot; grid allows players to anticipate the crash risk of any weight placed anywhere.&amp;#10;Playing risky moves away from the center of balance can win advantages or eliminate penalties.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;GAMEPLAY BASICS:&amp;#10;A win is triggered once a player has deployed all their spaceships and space junk.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- Flip over a &amp;quot;mission&amp;quot; card to reveal a value.&amp;#10;- You must match that value with the weight value of any quantity of spaceships deployed anywhere onto the solar system.&amp;#10;- The farther from the center a ship is deployed, the greater the risk and greater the reward.&amp;#10;- You may &amp;quot;dock&amp;quot; (stack) them onto any other spaceship to have their values added together towards making the required match.&amp;#10;- Get a space junk penalty piece if unable to make a match or by causing a crash.&amp;#10;- After a crash, the empty solar system gets re-balanced to continue the game.&amp;#10;- Get rid of your space junk or risk being eliminated by getting a 2nd one.&amp;#10;- Strategically manage the deployment of your light and heavy ships as your fleet diminishes while the game advances.&amp;#10;- Look for or create opportunities to deploy into high risk zones to gain significant advantages or eliminate a penalty.&amp;#10;- Tactically play special utility devices anytime during a mission.&amp;#10;- Ruthlessly capture an opponent's resources by docking onto their spaceship.&amp;#10;- You can choose one of three play options instead of choosing a mission:&amp;#10;1) Jettison a piece of space junk.&amp;#10;2) Take back a needed spaceship.&amp;#10;3) Swap an un-deployed heavy ship for its equivalent weight from your lighter ships that have been deployed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Play at your own risk!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
